          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1618924565802-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Whilst the onion is softening, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span>[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1618924586317-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1618924586317-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1618924586317-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1618924586317-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1618924586317-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion is starting to soften, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>sliced tomatoes </strong>and cook for a further 3-4 min</p><p>Add your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock</strong>, <strong>finely chopped tomatoes </strong>and <strong>drained lentils </strong>with your <strong>ground cinnamon</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat, and once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 5-6 min until thickened – this is your <strong>lentil filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1618924667958-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
